        "authors": "Branimir Bajt",
        "description": "CodeMap is a Roslyn-powered MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that turns any MCP-compatible AI agent into a semantic code navigator for C# and VB.NET solutions.\n\nInstead of reading source files, agents call 26 focused MCP tools to query symbols, call graphs, type hierarchies, and architectural facts (HTTP endpoints, config keys, DB tables, DI registrations, middleware, retry policies, log templates) — directly from a Roslyn-built semantic index. Mixed-language solutions (.sln / .slnx containing both C# and VB.NET projects) are indexed in a single pass.\n\nAverage token savings: 90%+ vs raw file reading. On production codebases: 95–99%+.\n\nKey capabilities:\n- symbols.search / symbols.get_card / symbols.get_context — find and understand any symbol\n- graph.trace_feature — full annotated feature flow in one call\n- refs.find / graph.callers / graph.callees — precise reference and call chain navigation\n- codemap.summarize / codemap.export / index.diff — codebase overview and semantic PR diffs\n- Workspace mode — see uncommitted edits via incremental overlay (~63ms refresh)\n- Shared baseline cache — index once, reuse across machines (CODEMAP_CACHE_DIR)\n\nUsage: add 'codemap-mcp' as an MCP server in your AI agent config. See README for setup.",
        "licenseExpression": "",
        "licenseUrl": "https://www.nuget.org/packages/codemap-mcp/1.4.0/license",
        "readmeUrl": "https://www.nuget.org/packages/codemap-mcp/1.4.0#show-readme-container"
      },
